<tr>
<td colspan="2">
<span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: red">Recruitment for Five Rings are opened.</span></span></span>
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="color: yellow"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: normal">Steps to Apply</span></span>
<br />
<span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: normal">
<br />
1. Look up your class's need and requirements.
<br />
2. Review the general requirements
<br />
3. Send your application to <span style="font-weight: bold"><a href="mailto:joining@five-rings.com">joining@five-rings.com</a></span>.  Your application should contain detailed information and <span style="font-weight: bold">MUST</span> include:
<br />
 <li>An up-to-date Magelo profile of yours (This includes proper AC, Attack and a link that actually works)
<br />
 <li>Your play times with time zones 
<br />
 <li>A short history of guilds you've been in and why you left
<br />
 <li>Whether or not you are the original owner of your character
<br />
 <li>Expansions you have
<br />
 <li>Raid Experience
<br />
 <li>Why do you want to join Five Rings?
<br />
And also any and all accesses you currently have. Stress is on DS, CoA, Vule, and Auras/Spells for PoR as well as <span style="font-weight: bold">ToB access</span>
<br />
4. You will usually receive an email reply that or the following night explaining what is next, please contact <span style="font-weight: bold">(Zymmer, Muolalas, or Anokin)</span> after you submit your app. If still have any other questions, please feel free to contact any officer (Leonardoe, Aikthin, Woodkinz). It is up to you to contact an officer after you submit your app to confirm that we actually received your application. Please do so in game.
<br />
5. Applications that do not contain <span style="text-decoration: underline"><span style="font-weight: bold">ALL</span></span> items listed in point #3 will be deleted and ignored. If you post your own application or write a shabby application, it will be deleted and ignored.</span></span>
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: normal"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Class Need &amp; AA requirements</span></span></span>
<br />

<br />
 <li> Bard ~ Medium
<br />
 <li> Beastlord ~ Very Low - Exceptional AA's + High Playtimes
<br />
 <li> Berserker ~ Medium 
<br />
 <li> Cleric ~ Very High
<br />
 <li> Druid ~ Medium 
<br />
 <li> Enchanter ~ Very High 
<br />
 <li> Magician ~ High 
<br />
 <li> Monk ~ Very Low - Exceptional AA's + High Playtimes
<br />
 <li> Necromancer ~ High 
<br />
 <li> Paladin ~ Very Low - Exceptional AA's + High Playtimes
<br />
 <li> Ranger ~ Medium 
<br />
 <li> Rogue ~ Medium 
<br />
 <li> Shadow Knight ~ Very Low - Exceptional AA's + High Playtimes
<br />
 <li> Shaman ~ Medium 
<br />
 <li> Warrior ~ Low 
<br />
 <li> Wizard ~ High 
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline"><span style="color: Red"><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: normal"> The amount of AA required of your class is subject to change at the discretion of the applicant officer with advice from the current members of that class.  Meeting the posted aa requirement does not guarantee an app period.
<br />
</span></span></span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: normal"><span style="text-decoration: underline">General Requirements</span></span></span>
<br />

<br />
1. You must be able to raid during our primary raiding hours of <span style="font-weight: bold">6pm - 12am Eastern Time</span>
<br />

<br />
2. We expect you to be lvl 70 before applying.
<br />

<br />
3. <span style="font-weight: bold">50% raid attendance is the standard MINIMUM for guilding</span>. If your plans are to show up consistantly, just to complete your app process, then we see a steady decline in your playtimes, the possibility of guild removal is probable.
<br />

<br />
4. As a raiding guild, we require members to raid with us when they are online. Skipping raids while online is not permissible without a plausible excuse. We do not allow members to log on and be afk or not participating in raids for extended periods of time.
<br />

<br />
5. You must respect other players in the game. We don't want loudmouths, drama queens or sociopaths.  If you can't control yourself in the game or on our message boards (or other public message boards) you will be subject to punishment and possibly removal from the guild.
<br />

<br />
6. Can you handle failure? Sometimes we will fail multiple times before we succeed once. Are you the type of person that will be negative or will you add some constructive imput to an encounter? Being negative only brings everyone down around you.
<br />

<br />
7. You <span style="font-weight: bold">MUST</span> minimally have <span style="font-weight: bold">All</span> current expansions.
<br />

<br />
8. Apps should have between 200-250 AA's (<span style="font-weight: bold">MINIMUM</span>) and will be required to pick up raid specific AA's defined by guilded members of that class. Exceptions will be made <span style="font-weight: bold">solemnly</span> depending on the demand for classes. 
<br />

<br />
9. You will remain an applicant untill you are flagged for Anguish, and Dreadspire but for 30 days as sponsored applicant at the least. We expect you to obtain those things that can be obtained through experience groups. 
<br />

<br />
11. Can get at least over 160 in all resistance unbuffed.
<br />

<br />
12. Download Maps <a href="http://maps.eq-toolbox.com/" target="_blank">http://maps.eq-toolbox.com/</a>
<br />
. You must be able to get around places in the game. Complaining about not knowing how to get to certain places is not an excuse. It slows us down. Also try communicating in group and find out if anyone has the group leader aa (find pc). Chances are a person with this skill knows exactly where to be. The illuminated path dirrects you right to anyone in your group.
<br />

<br />
13. If you are missing some of these requirements, but consider yourself an exceptional player, please feel free to contact (Zymmer, Muolalas or Anokin), and they can discuss these possibilities with you.
<br />

<br />
14. In addition you should be working on or have obtained your 55/70 auras as well as spells for PoR
<br />

<br />
15. You MUST be guildless when you send in an application
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: normal"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Application Process</span></span></span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Pre-screening:</span> Your application will be posted in full to an internal forum where current members will comment on it.  If the comments are not overwhelmingly negative, you will receive raid clearance.  This phase can last between 24 hours and up to 4 days.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Raiding:</span> You may raid with the guild with or without sponsorship.  You will receive a guild invitation and remain guilded for your entire application.  While unsponsored you should be on your best behavior as you will most likely have your application terminated if engage in questionable behavior.  Bad first impressions are hard to undo.  If you do not obtain a sponsor within 10 days to 2 weeks of raid clearance, your application <span style="font-style: italic"><span style="text-decoration: underline">may</span></span> be closed.  While raiding, members will be evaluating your performance and posting comments on your application thread.  This phase can last between 4 to 6 weeks.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Voting:</span> Once the guild or your sponsor agrees you are ready for a vote, a poll will be opened.  Under normal circumstances you will be guilded if you obtain a strong majority of yes votes from a minimum of 35 votes.  If you do not obtain the required percentage of votes to be guilded, the membership officer may call for a revote.  In either case, if you do not obtain the required percentage of yes votes, your application will be closed and you will be dismissed.  This phase can last from 3 to 10 days.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: normal"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Sponsorship</span></span></span>
<br />

<br />
You have two options for sponsorship: 1) A sole sponsor who is of your class, or someone that is very well versed in your roles on raids and able to coach and guide you to success. 2) A sponsor who is not of your class and <span style="text-decoration: underline">a co-sponsor who is of your class.  </span>Primarily your sponsor keeps track of your flag progression and helps you along the application process.  A sponsor/co-sponsor of the same class will help you with questions you have about your class's role on raids and gives general class playing advice. You do not need a sponsor to apply, but one should be obtained within the first week or so of your application.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: normal"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Cross-server Applications</span></span></span>
<br />

<br />
Yes, we accept cross server applications.  If you're great at your class, have a 200+ AAs and you play all the time and have no major personality disorders then there shouldn't be a problem.  We may be more lax on our restrictions because you have chosen to leave your former server, but you still must prove to be valuable to our guild.
<br />

<br />
We will do a formal check on all cross-server transfer applicants. Those with bad reputation are not welcomed in Five Rings. We also may ask for references.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: normal"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Application Caveat</span></span></span>
<br />

<br />
If you've applied to this guild under false pretenses, your application will be closed immediately and you will be removed from the guild once evidence has been discovered.  False pretenses include: applying on behalf of someone else (i.e. playing a character you're not skilled in or allowing someone else to regularly play your character), applying to steal strategies, applying to more than one guild at the same time, and applying to loot gear and leave. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: normal"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Loot</span></span></span>
<br />

<br />
You will have a chance to pick up loot as an applicant.  We are a DKP guild and you will earn DKP at the same rate as members when raiding with us.  You will receive loot if all members on the raid pass on an item.  We encourage applicants to obtain better gear, as zones we currently raid in are very unforgiving to those with weak gear.  Upon being guilded we will deduct a small amount of DKP as a &quot;guilding charge.&quot;  If you have serious issues with loot distribution in a DKP system, then apply to another guild. We've heard the arguments.  We don't want to hear them again.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: normal"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Backflags</span></span></span>
<br />

<br />
We have backflagging arrangements with some other guilds to facilitate applicants in catching up.  You should at all times, drop what you are doing in game if a backflag mob is called by us or with another guild.  Your primary responsibilty as an applicant is to get flags so you can raid where we do.  While obtaining backflags with another guild you represent Five Rings and are a guest.  Do not make demands of the other guild nor do anything you are not specifically asked to do.  If our officers receive a complaint and find it to be severe, your application will be terminated.  
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: normal"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Tips for Being a Successful Applicant</span></span></span>
<br />

<br />
1. Play often. If you play for two hours a day two days a week, then it's unlikely you will attain full membership. Raiding requires having a dependable number of people online during raid times.  Raiding is almost a second job and you're only paid with the satisfaction of completing a difficult task as a team.
<br />

<br />
2. Get your flags. These are the following flags you would need to raid with us: CoA, all 7 Anguish signets, Dreadspire, and ToB. If you can't be on early or often for some reason, then give your login information to someone you trust in the guild.  If we have commited ourselves to 15 backflag events in one months time and you only have 2 or 3 flags, it will not look favorable when it comes time for your vote.
<br />

<br />
3. Enjoy playing, even when you fail. If you don't enjoy Everquest as a game, then you won't enjoy raiding. If you take failure badly, then raiding probably won't please you, because it often requires failures in order to learn and progress.
<br />

<br />
4. Be attentive. Raiding often requires following a set of instructions.  If you can't follow instructions or don't take the time to read them, then you are likely to screw up and cause the raid to fail. So pay attention when the time for explanation comes and ask questions if your task is unclear. And yes, one person can cause an entire raid to fail.
<br />

<br />
5. Be at the keyboard. If you AFK constantly to tend to your kids, stop your cats from climbing the curtains or perform dental procedures in your illegal, uninsured home office, we don't have a need for you.  We depend on you to be at your computer and do your task when it comes time.
<br />

<br />
6. Be helpful and selfless. Offer to help others out, but don't expect help in return. If someone needs a rez or corpse summon in a remote zone, go help them. If you're not doing anything, offer to help farm items for someone or get them a flag.  If no one is willing to help, don't get upset.  Everyone likes to enjoy their free time and do their own thing.
<br />

<br />
7. Let us know when you are away. If you have to leave the world of Everquest for a short period of time due to whatever reason you have, inform us. Let us know what is going on with you so any misunderstandings can be avoided.
<br />

<br />
8. Teamwork; espeically those within your class. Teamwork is by far one of the most important elements that we expect from players. Everquest is a team game, not an individual one. If you cannot work well with other members; and especially those that are the same class as you, chances are, voting will not look favorable. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: normal"><span style="text-decoration: underline">General Information</span></span></span>
<br />

<br />
Our guild goals at the moment include clearing Demiplane and PoR. We still raid CoA, DoN dragons, and the very occasional Tacvi
<br />

<br />
If you have read this and agree to the terms, please reply with an acknowledgement.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
